    <div class=\"shortcode_info\">\n              <h2>Authentication</h2>\n              \n    <h4 class=\"s_title\">API key</h4>\n      <p class=\"mb-30\">\n        \n        An API key is a special token (Qor-Client-Key) that you need to provide in header when making API calls, Like:\n        <code> { Qor-Client-Key: \"TOKEN_VALUE\" }</code>\n      \n      </p>\n    \n  \n    <h4 class=\"s_title\">API key</h4>\n      <p class=\"mb-30\">\n        \n        An API key is a special token (Qor-App-Key) that you need to provide in header when making API calls, Like:\n        <code> { Qor-App-Key: \"TOKEN_VALUE\" }</code>\n      \n      </p>\n    \n  \n          </div>\n          <div class=\"border_bottom\"></div>\n      </article>\n    \r\n                            \n                <div class=\"wtree\">\n    <ul>\n      <li>\n        <span>\n          <b style=\"display: flex;\">transaction_data <i class=\"red\" style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b>\n          <i class=\"api-path mb-30\"><span style=\"\"><span class=\"api-method api-method-get\">get</span> <span class=api-path-root>https://api-sandbox.qorcommerce.io/v3</span> <span class=api-path-name>/customers</span> </span><span class=api-path-try-btn data-id=Customers-get-customers>Try Out</span></p><ul class=\"nav nav-tabs\" id=Customers-get-customers-tabs role=tablist><li class=nav-item><a class=\"nav-link active\" id=Customers-get-customers-request-tab data-toggle=tab href=#Customers-get-customers-request role=tab aria-controls=Customers-get-customers-request aria-selected=true><i class=\"fas fa-arrow-alt-circle-right\" style=\"color: #00BCD4;\"></i> Request</a></li><li class=nav-item><a class=nav-link id=Customers-get-customers-response-tab fade show active\" id=Customers-get-customers-request role=tabpanel aria-labelledby=Customers-get-customers-request-tab><p class=request-name>query</p><div class=request-box><div class=request-box-value><div class=request-box-name>cust_id <span class=request-box-optional>OPTIONAL</span></div><div class=request-box-details><p class=request-box-type>string</p><p class=request-box-description>Search for customer by `id`. Separate multiple id filters with a `,` (comma).<br><br>**Example:** `635, 732`</p><p></p></div></div><div class=border_bottom></div><div class=request-box-value><div class=request-box-name>first_name <span class=request-box-optional>OPTIONAL</span></div><div class=request-box-details><p class=request-box-type>string</p><p class=request-box-description>Case-insensitive search for customers by first name. Separate multiple first_name filters with a `,` (comma).<br><br>**Example:** `\"James, Sally, Mitch\"`</p><p></p></div></div><div class=border_bottom></div><div class=request-box-value><div class=request-box-name>last_name <span class=request-box-optional>OPTIONAL</span></div><div class=request-box-details><p class=request-box-type>string</p><p class=request-box-description>Case-insensitive search for customers by last name. Separate multiple last_name filters with a `,` (comma).<br><br>**Example:** `\"Brown, O'Brein, Contenelli\"`</p><p></p></div></div><div class=border_bottom></div><div class=request-box-value><div class=request-box-name>address <span class=request-box-optional>OPTIONAL</span></div><div class=request-box-details><p class=request-box-type>string</p><p class=request-box-description>Case-insensitive search for customers by street address. Partial input allowed.<br><br>**Example:** `Main` will return all customers that have **Main** in their street address.</p><p></p></div></div><div class=border_bottom></div><div class=request-box-value><div class=request-box-name>address2 <span class=request-box-optional>OPTIONAL</span></div><div class=request-box-details><p class=request-box-type>string</p><p class=request-box-description>Case-insensitive search for customers by second street address. Partial input allowed.<br><br>**Example:** `Apt` will return all customers that have **Apt** in their secondary street address.</p><p></p></div></div><div class=border_bottom></div><div class=request-box-value><div class=request-box-name>city <span class=request-box-optional>OPTIONAL</span></div><div class=request-box-details><p class=request-box-type>string</p><p class=request-box-description>Case-insensitive search for customers by city name. Separate multiple city name filters with a `,` (comma).<br><br>**Example:** `\"Los Angeles, Miami, Lake Arrowhead\"`</p><p></p></div></div><div class=border_bottom></div><div class=request-box-value><div class=request-box-name>state <span class=request-box-optional>OPTIONAL</span></div><div class=request-box-details><p class=request-box-type>string</p><p class=request-box-description>Case-insensitive search for customers by ISO 2-digit state code. Separate multiple state code filters with a `,` (comma).<br><br>**Example, `\"CA, MN, GA\"`</p><p></p></div></div><div class=border_bottom></div><div class=request-box-value><div class=request-box-name>zip <span class=request-box-optional>OPTIONAL</span></div><div class=request-box-details><p class=request-box-type>string</p><p class=request-box-description>customer address zip code</p><p></p></div></div><div class=border_bottom></div><div class=request-box-value><div class=request-box-name>country <span class=request-box-optional>OPTIONAL</span></div><div class=request-box-details><p class=request-box-type>string</p><p class=request-box-description>Case-insensitive search for customers by ISO 2-digit country code. Separate multiple country code filters with a `,` (comma).<br><br>**Example:** `\"US, CA, RD\"`</p><p></p></div></div><div class=border_bottom></div><div class=request-box-value><div class=request-box-name>email <span class=request-box-optional>OPTIONAL</span></div><div class=request-box-details><p class=request-box-type>string</p><p class=request-box-description>Case-insensitive search for customers by email address. Partial input allowed. For example, `example.com` will return all customers that have **example.com** in their email address. Separate multiple email filters with a `,` (comma).<br><br>**Example:** `\"example.com, sally@company.com, .net\"`</p><p></p></div></div><div class=border_bottom></div><div class=request-box-value><div class=request-box-name>phone_number <span class=request-box-optional>OPTIONAL</span></div><div class=request-box-details><p class=request-box-type>string</p><p class=request-box-description>Case-insensitive search for customers by phone number. Partial input allowed.<br><br>**Example:** `213` will return all customers that have **213** in their phone number</p><p></p></div></div><div class=border_bottom></div><div class=request-box-value><div class=request-box-name>company_name <span class=request-box-optional>OPTIONAL</span></div><div class=request-box-details><p class=request-box-type>string</p><p class=request-box-description>Case-insensitive search for customers by company name. Partial matches provided. For example, `bro` will return all customers that have **bro** in their their company name. Separate multiple company_name filters with a `,` (comma).<br><br>**Example:** `\"bro, Acme Plumbing, Hatfield & McCoy\"`</p><p></p></div></div><div class=border_bottom></div><div class=request-box-value><div class=request-box-name>web_address <span class=request-box-optional>OPTIONAL</span></div><div class=request-box-details><p class=request-box-type>string</p><p class=request-box-description>Case-insensitive search for customers by website address. Partial matches provided. For example, `jan` will return all customers that have **jan** in their their website address. style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>object</i></span><ul><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">descriptor <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The name under which the merchant is doing business.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">annualCCSales <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: The value of annual credit card sales for this merchant. The value is an integer in cents so '25.30' will be '2530'</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">avgTicket <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: The value of average credit card sales for this merchant. The value is an integer in cents so '25.30' will be '2530'</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">environment <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The environment the merchant is in. Possible request values are `retail`, `moto`, `supermarket`, `cardPresent`, `restaurant`, `serviceStation`, `fuel` and `ecommerce`</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">mcc <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The Merchant Category Code of this merchant. Contact dev ops for proper codes</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">merchant <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>object</i></span><ul><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">type <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: The type of merchant that this merchant is. Possible request values are `0`(Sole Proprietor), `1`(Corporation), `2`(Limited Liability Company), `3`(Partnership), `5`(Non-Profit Organization) and `6`(Government Organization)</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">name <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The name of this merchant.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">address1 <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The first line of the address associated with this merchant.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">address2 </b><i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The second line of the address associated with this merchant.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">city <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The city associated with this merchant.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">state <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The state associated with this merchant. Must be the state's two letter abbreviation</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">zip <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: The zip code associated with this merchant.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">country <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The country associated with this merchant. Currently only accepts `USA`</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">timezone <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The timezone associated with this merchant. Possible request values are `est`, `cst`, `pst`, `mst`, `akst`, `hst`, `sst`, `chst` and `ast`</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">phone <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: The phone number associated with this merchant.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">email <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The email associated with this merchant.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">ein <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: The IRS Employer Number associated with this merchant.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">website <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The website url associated with this merchant.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">locations <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: The number of locations this merchant has.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">public <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: Indicates whether or not this merchant is publicly held.</i></span></li><ul><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">account <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>object</i></span><ul><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">method <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: this account's type. Possible request values are `8`(Checking), `9`(Savings), `10`(Corporate Checking) and `11`(Corporate Savings)</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">number <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The bank number of this account.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">routing <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The routing number of this account.</i></span></li></ul></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">currency <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The currency type this merchant is using. Only accepts `USD`</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">primary <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: Indicates whether or not this account is the primary account of this merchant. Possible request values are `0` and `1`</i></span></li></ul></ul></li></ul></li><ul><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">title <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The title for this owner.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">first <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The first name of this owner.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">last <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The last name of this owner.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">dob <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: The date of birth of this owner. The field is in the form `YYYYMMDD`</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">email <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The email associated with this owner.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">ownership <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: The percent ownership that this owner has. The field is represented as basis points, so 80% would be 8000</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">timezone <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The timezone associated with this owner. Possible request values are `est`, `cst`, `pst`, `mst`, `akst`, `hst`, `sst`, `chst` and `ast`</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">address1 <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The first line of the address associated with this owner.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">address2 </b><i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The second line address associated with this owner.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">city <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The city associated with this owner.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">state <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The state associated with this owner. style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>object</i></span><ul><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">descriptor <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The name under which the merchant is doing business.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">annualCCSales </b><i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: The value of annual credit card sales for this merchant. The value is an integer in cents so '25.30' will be '2530'</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">avgTicket </b><i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: The value of average credit card sales for this merchant. The value is an integer in cents so '25.30' will be '2530'</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">mcc </b><i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The Merchant Category Code of this merchant. Contact dev ops for proper codes</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">merchant <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>object</i></span><ul><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">type <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: The type of merchant that this merchant is. Possible request values are `0`(Sole Proprietor), `1`(Corporation), `2`(Limited Liability Company), `3`(Partnership), `5`(Non-Profit Organization) and `6`(Government Organization)</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">name <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The name of this merchant.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">address1 <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The first line of the address associated with this merchant.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">address2 </b><i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The second line of the address associated with this merchant.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">city <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The city associated with this merchant.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">state <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The state associated with this merchant. Must be the state's two letter abbreviation</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">zip <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: The zip code associated with this merchant.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">country <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The country associated with this merchant. Currently only accepts `USA`</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">timezone <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The timezone associated with this merchant. Possible request values are `est`, `cst`, `pst`, `mst`, `akst`, `hst`, `sst`, `chst` and `ast`</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">phone <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: The phone number associated with this merchant.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">email <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The email associated with this merchant.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">ein <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: The IRS Employer Number / SSN associated with this merchant.</i></span></li><ul><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">account <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>object</i></span><ul><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">method <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: this account's type. Possible request values are `8`(Checking), `9`(Savings), `10`(Corporate Checking) and `11`(Corporate Savings)</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">number <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The bank number of this account.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">routing <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The routing number of this account.</i></span></li></ul></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">currency <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The currency type this merchant is using. Only accepts `USD`</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">primary <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: Indicates whether or not this account is the primary account of this merchant. Possible request values are `0` and `1`</i></span></li></ul></ul></li></ul></li><ul><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">title <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The title for this owner.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">first <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The first name of this owner.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">last <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The last name of this owner.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">dob <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: The date of birth of this owner. The field is in the form `YYYYMMDD`</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">email <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The email associated with this owner.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">ownership <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>integer</i> <i>Description: The percent ownership that this owner has. The field is represented as basis points, so 80% would be 8000</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">timezone <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The timezone associated with this owner. Possible request values are `est`, `cst`, `pst`, `mst`, `akst`, `hst`, `sst`, `chst` and `ast`</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">address1 <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The first line of the address associated with this owner.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">address2 </b><i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The second line address associated with this owner.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">city <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The city associated with this owner.</i></span></li><li><span><b style=\"display: flex;\">state <i class=red style=\"margin-left: 2px;\">*</i></b> <i class=object-type>string</i> <i>Description: The state associated with this owner.
